So he's just going to be observing us and taking it.

02:14:48.300 --> 02:14:53.660
So I take the jump seat behind the, you know, pilot and just fly with John.

02:14:53.960 --> 02:14:58.180
Did he talk to you about UFOs before you got the job at S4 Area 51?

02:14:58.700 --> 02:15:01.880
No, it didn't talk to me about him, but I mean, he spoke about them.

02:15:01.880 --> 02:15:03.000
Did he ever?

02:15:03.260 --> 02:15:10.720
Yeah, I mean, he used to tell me there are aliens living in the mountains alongside, you know, I think it's I-95 or something.

02:15:10.800 --> 02:15:11.040
Right.

02:15:11.120 --> 02:15:11.520
The highway.

02:15:11.720 --> 02:15:13.860
He said, yeah, there's a billion of them in there.

02:15:14.660 --> 02:15:15.720
It's so crazy.

02:15:16.040 --> 02:15:19.260
Did he ever show you anything Billy Myers related?

02:15:20.540 --> 02:15:24.240
I don't, I don't recall.

02:15:24.560 --> 02:15:24.780
Okay.

02:15:24.780 --> 02:15:36.880
I think, I think when I described, I think when I described the craft to him and drew it, I think he brought out the Billy Myers book and he said, I think that's where I, in fact, it is.

02:15:36.940 --> 02:15:38.040
That's where I first saw it.

02:15:38.040 --> 02:15:40.680
So we saw, uh, we showed him the Billy Myers tape.

02:15:40.820 --> 02:15:43.500
I said, yeah, that's, that's not like the craft.

02:15:43.640 --> 02:15:44.440
That's the craft.

02:15:45.080 --> 02:15:45.980
That's so interesting.

02:15:46.260 --> 02:15:48.020
So yeah, he kind of helped you piece it together.

02:15:48.160 --> 02:15:55.460
Is, did he, um, was he still affiliated with, cause he was a CIA cargo pilot till 1983, I think.

02:15:55.480 --> 02:15:56.080
Yeah, that's true.

02:15:56.080 --> 02:16:00.940
Did he, uh, continue flying for them after that or did he disappear?

02:16:01.280 --> 02:16:01.520
Okay.

02:16:01.680 --> 02:16:02.900
I don't think so.

02:16:03.160 --> 02:16:03.420
Yeah.

02:16:03.780 --> 02:16:09.820
Cause he was, he's this interesting character to me because it seems like he has crazy access to area 51.

02:16:09.960 --> 02:16:13.360
Like he's like snooping around and taking photos of like F-117s.

02:16:13.460 --> 02:16:21.540
And he even leaks the details of the F-117 to George Knapp, but then he still like knows all the security guards there.

02:16:21.660 --> 02:16:23.780
So I'm like, what's his, what's his deal?

02:16:24.020 --> 02:16:24.220
You know?

02:16:24.220 --> 02:16:34.660
I mean, I had been out at, you know, but before the S-4 thing, um, you know, out in the desert in the middle of the night with binoculars and stuff trying outside, uh, Tonopah.

02:16:34.980 --> 02:16:35.200
Yeah.

02:16:35.380 --> 02:16:39.320
You know, trying to get pictures of any new aircraft that's flying around.

02:16:39.500 --> 02:16:42.400
Cause I mean, he was obviously a big aviation buff.

02:16:42.580 --> 02:16:42.820
Yeah.

02:16:42.920 --> 02:16:44.340
You know, and I was into that too.

02:16:44.420 --> 02:16:49.560
Sometimes I'd just go out and watch, you know, fighters taken off from Nellis Air Force Base.

02:16:49.560 --> 02:16:51.400
Cause you could get right up to the fence there.

02:16:51.400 --> 02:16:59.640
And, and, uh, you know, so it was, uh, yeah, he was definitely into snooping around and saying whatever he could find out.

02:16:59.840 --> 02:17:02.840
I, uh, I mentioned Jacques Vallée, uh, earlier.

02:17:03.340 --> 02:17:05.140
He, you met him, right?

02:17:05.760 --> 02:17:06.220
Yeah.

02:17:06.220 --> 02:17:08.760
I met him and, you know, we spoke briefly.

02:17:08.760 --> 02:17:20.520
And then, uh, um, from what I remember, uh, somebody was talking about making a movie with him.

02:17:20.860 --> 02:17:27.280
And then after hearing about me and talking, they started talking about, well, maybe we won't, we'll do it on Bob instead.

02:17:27.280 --> 02:17:29.780
And he was super pissed off.

02:17:30.020 --> 02:17:30.180
Really?

02:17:30.480 --> 02:17:30.780
Yeah.

02:17:30.780 --> 02:17:35.940
And then from that point on, all of a sudden, you know, everything Bob said is crazy.

02:17:36.220 --> 02:17:36.620
Really?

02:17:36.920 --> 02:17:37.100
Yeah.

02:17:37.600 --> 02:17:40.020
But, uh, yeah, initially he was, uh.

02:17:40.340 --> 02:17:49.680
Cause, cause yeah, he writes, he wrote a book called Messengers of Deception and he writes about you and he says, um, you know, Bob Lazar seems to be very legit.

02:17:49.680 --> 02:17:57.800
But, uh, he also talks about this pine salt drink he drinks, you know, this, this drink he drinks and the memory lapses it caused.

02:17:58.080 --> 02:17:58.560
Now what?

02:17:58.800 --> 02:17:59.720
There's no memory.

02:17:59.760 --> 02:18:00.440
No memory lapses.

02:18:00.460 --> 02:18:01.460
That's a bunch of nonsense.

02:18:01.860 --> 02:18:02.000
Okay.

02:18:02.200 --> 02:18:03.520
That's a bunch of, it's, you know.

02:18:04.160 --> 02:18:07.440
So it was like this vitamin B shot that was like immunity related.

02:18:07.740 --> 02:18:07.760
Yeah.

02:18:07.840 --> 02:18:08.060
Yeah.

02:18:08.100 --> 02:18:09.060
That's all it was.

02:18:09.080 --> 02:18:09.300
Okay.

02:18:09.400 --> 02:18:12.760
Again, you know, we're working with completely unknown materials.

02:18:13.000 --> 02:18:13.140
Yeah.

02:18:13.200 --> 02:18:16.160
We don't know what, and apparently people had severe reactions.

02:18:16.440 --> 02:18:16.620
Yeah.

02:18:16.680 --> 02:18:18.700
To some of this stuff, just touching the craft.

02:18:19.700 --> 02:18:20.540
So yeah.

02:18:20.940 --> 02:18:22.400
So they had dealt with that before.

02:18:22.740 --> 02:18:26.180
I feel like I can defend you on 99.9% of things.

02:18:26.420 --> 02:18:29.460
And then the one thing I have trouble with is the MIT thing.

02:18:29.540 --> 02:18:33.980
Cause that's the other thing circulating is it was, did you get your master's there or you were sent there?

02:18:34.040 --> 02:18:34.920
I was sent there.

02:18:34.960 --> 02:18:37.340
On a specific kind of program, isolated program.

02:18:37.340 --> 02:18:37.500
Yeah.

02:18:37.900 --> 02:18:38.160
And then.

02:18:38.360 --> 02:18:38.380
Yeah.

02:18:38.400 --> 02:18:42.420
And I did, I did a lot of auditing in both places.

02:18:42.780 --> 02:18:45.680
And then on, on Caltech for Caltech, what was that?

02:18:45.680 --> 02:18:49.140
So you were sent to MIT and then Caltech was different.

02:18:49.300 --> 02:18:50.680
Caltech was way before that.

02:18:50.820 --> 02:18:51.060
Okay.

02:18:51.200 --> 02:18:53.060
That was, you know, but, um.

02:18:55.100 --> 02:18:55.480
And now.

02:18:55.600 --> 02:18:55.820
I don't know.

02:18:55.900 --> 02:19:01.480
I guess if I really look through old paperwork and stuff, I can come up with things, but that's

02:19:01.480 --> 02:19:02.180
never been.

02:19:02.300 --> 02:19:02.600
Yeah.

02:19:02.600 --> 02:19:07.440
And I think George Knapp found, I think some people who knew you at Caltech.

02:19:07.440 --> 02:19:07.460
Yeah.

02:19:07.460 --> 02:19:08.000
I mean.

02:19:08.060 --> 02:19:08.260
Yeah.

02:19:08.380 --> 02:19:08.620
Yeah.

02:19:08.920 --> 02:19:09.140
Yeah.

02:19:09.820 --> 02:19:17.560
One other question that people have is why were you allowed to give him a tour of Los Alamos

02:19:17.560 --> 02:19:21.300
after, uh, you know, you blew the whistle on area 51?

02:19:21.440 --> 02:19:25.020
Like, why wasn't there this like nationwide directive at all of the national labs?

02:19:25.060 --> 02:19:26.440
Like, don't let this guy back.

02:19:26.440 --> 02:19:28.600
Like, and look, it was really nothing.

02:19:28.600 --> 02:19:35.020
I mean, we got on a Southwest flight, came out there, rented a car, drove up.

02:19:35.420 --> 02:19:39.380
And, uh, I still knew all the guards and stuff like that.

02:19:39.520 --> 02:19:42.660
So we came up and he's, you know, it's like, Lazar, you're back.

02:19:42.780 --> 02:19:43.020
Yeah.

02:19:43.220 --> 02:19:45.200
Just going in there to, you know.

02:19:45.200 --> 02:19:47.300
So you think it was just like, it was just like a different time.

02:19:47.680 --> 02:19:47.800
And.

02:19:48.320 --> 02:19:49.200
Oh, it's, you can't.

02:19:49.500 --> 02:19:52.440
Los Alamos is so much higher security now.

02:19:52.440 --> 02:19:58.380
I mean, it was so nonchalant back then and we just wrote right into the experimental

02:19:58.380 --> 02:20:01.100
areas, came over, hey, I was at Georgia, this is my desk.

02:20:01.600 --> 02:20:02.120
Were you surprised?

02:20:02.260 --> 02:20:04.960
Was it part of you nervous that there would be some red alert?

02:20:05.600 --> 02:20:06.440
No, not at all.

02:20:06.680 --> 02:20:07.300
You were like.

02:20:07.380 --> 02:20:08.260
Zero concern.

02:20:08.400 --> 02:20:12.380
You didn't worry that there was any sort of coordination between area 51 and Los Alamos.

02:20:12.380 --> 02:20:13.920
Nobody knew what was going on there.

02:20:14.060 --> 02:20:16.580
It was just, like I said, it was very lax atmosphere.

02:20:16.580 --> 02:20:24.200
In fact, a year or two after that, they were so concerned about that.

02:20:24.280 --> 02:20:30.540
I think they called it the Tiger Team came in to test security there and they failed so

02:20:30.540 --> 02:20:35.240
horribly that they just redid everything.

02:20:36.100 --> 02:20:40.300
And, you know, after that point, you're, forget it, you're not going in.

02:20:40.420 --> 02:20:44.000
But, yeah, I like still had keys and things.

02:20:45.000 --> 02:20:45.940
Yeah, it was.

02:20:46.580 --> 02:20:48.480
It was not even a problem.

02:20:48.720 --> 02:20:50.640
When did you start United Nuclear?

02:20:52.300 --> 02:20:53.780
99, 2000.

02:20:54.260 --> 02:20:57.420
Did you ever work with the government with United Nuclear?

02:20:57.740 --> 02:20:58.060
Yeah, yeah.

02:20:58.160 --> 02:20:58.420
Oh, yeah.

02:20:58.440 --> 02:20:58.700
Okay.

02:20:58.940 --> 02:20:59.100
Yeah.

02:20:59.340 --> 02:21:05.700
I mean, we still, we supply them, you know, they train Department of Homeland Security,

02:21:06.040 --> 02:21:06.480
FBI.

02:21:06.940 --> 02:21:12.700
I mean, we sell them stuff all the time, especially when they're training people to use radiation

02:21:12.700 --> 02:21:13.640
detection equipment.

02:21:13.640 --> 02:21:20.540
I mean, we'll give them or sell them, you know, radioactive sources so they can go hide

02:21:20.540 --> 02:21:24.620
something in a warehouse and give the trainees a Geiger counter, go find it, you know.

02:21:24.620 --> 02:21:31.180
Did you ever wonder why they didn't view you as a liability given your, you know, late

02:21:31.180 --> 02:21:35.660
80s experience at S4 Area 51 and they were just down to do contract work with you?

02:21:35.660 --> 02:21:37.660
I don't know.

02:21:38.220 --> 02:21:38.820
I don't know.

02:21:38.920 --> 02:21:42.160
You know, but one hand doesn't know what the other is doing in the government.

02:21:42.360 --> 02:21:42.800
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

02:21:43.140 --> 02:21:44.280
It's kind of a mess.

02:21:44.480 --> 02:21:45.000
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

02:21:45.060 --> 02:21:46.020
No, and it's a...

02:21:46.020 --> 02:21:52.000
I mean, in fact, part of, you know, United Nuclear, when it was just beginning, some

02:21:52.000 --> 02:21:53.760
of the stuff we're selling was kind of questionable.

02:21:54.380 --> 02:21:59.020
You know, this could potentially, you know, be used for explosives or stuff like that.

02:21:59.100 --> 02:21:59.220
Great.

02:21:59.220 --> 02:22:06.560
So, went down to the FBI and reviewed everything with them and they went, no, you can, that's

02:22:06.560 --> 02:22:06.780
cool.

02:22:06.900 --> 02:22:09.440
Went down to the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, and Firearms.

02:22:09.540 --> 02:22:14.140
No, we're good, you know, and the Postal Service, no, everything's good.

02:22:14.400 --> 02:22:14.900
All right, great.

02:22:14.920 --> 02:22:15.840
We're going to go sell on it.

02:22:16.360 --> 02:22:21.920
And then, you know, raided by the Consumer Product Safety Commission, they come in with

02:22:21.920 --> 02:22:23.200
a SWAT team with a machine.

02:22:23.340 --> 02:22:27.460
Woke my wife up out of bed with, you know, an M16 bindered in her face.

02:22:27.500 --> 02:22:28.220
Jesus Christ.

02:22:28.220 --> 02:22:30.820
You know, it's like, we checked with everybody.

02:22:31.000 --> 02:22:32.320
I didn't check with us.

02:22:32.720 --> 02:22:34.420
So, don't you guys talk?

02:22:34.600 --> 02:22:38.300
So, yeah, one hand has no idea what the other's doing when it comes to the government.

02:22:38.340 --> 02:22:39.460
Yeah, no, I believe that.

02:22:40.080 --> 02:22:47.020
Is there any part of you that thinks that they wanted you to come out and that they wanted

02:22:47.020 --> 02:22:48.740
some frameworks?

02:22:48.740 --> 02:22:53.320
Because, to your point, it's maladaptive to have this completely shut out from, like,

02:22:53.400 --> 02:22:57.100
to have a STEM student who's talented and, you know, some random state.

02:22:57.120 --> 02:22:57.740
Why go through the complicated...

02:22:58.220 --> 02:23:01.720
I mean, why make it complicated and make me do it?

02:23:01.820 --> 02:23:02.100
Right.

02:23:02.280 --> 02:23:03.600
Why not just do it yourself?

02:23:03.720 --> 02:23:06.040
Put out the high-level framework and say, yeah.

02:23:06.040 --> 02:23:10.140
This whole complicated scenario with this guy coming in and hope that he does something

02:23:10.140 --> 02:23:12.360
you want, that doesn't make any sense.

02:23:12.460 --> 02:23:13.040
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

02:23:13.040 --> 02:23:14.160
No, I think that's fair.

02:23:15.660 --> 02:23:21.700
There's this John Lear interview where, again, it's impossible to parse what the hell is

02:23:21.700 --> 02:23:22.600
going on with that guy.

02:23:22.780 --> 02:23:25.640
Look, I have heard John Lear tell my story.

02:23:25.740 --> 02:23:26.000
Yeah.

02:23:26.000 --> 02:23:27.660
And it is so wrong.

02:23:28.660 --> 02:23:29.960
It's unbelievable.

02:23:30.500 --> 02:23:31.000
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

02:23:31.000 --> 02:23:31.640
It's unbelievable.

02:23:31.920 --> 02:23:33.220
I mean, he puts...

02:23:33.220 --> 02:23:38.620
I mean, he inserts himself in there in a prominent position, you know, well, I got Bob, you know,

02:23:38.620 --> 02:23:40.280
to get the job to here and this.

02:23:40.520 --> 02:23:42.040
And what are you talking...

02:23:42.040 --> 02:23:43.500
It's completely inaccurate.

02:23:43.500 --> 02:23:44.620
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

02:23:45.020 --> 02:23:53.020
And in this interview, he says, like, yeah, Admiral McClellan, who was a Navy admiral, came

02:23:53.020 --> 02:23:58.420
to me and he was MJ level, you know, MJ obviously in the UFO lore would be like the elite, you

02:23:58.420 --> 02:24:03.480
know, kind of committee that governs this whole topic, came to me and he said, we got to get

02:24:03.480 --> 02:24:07.100
Bob on the job because we know that we can hide his...

02:24:07.100 --> 02:24:12.260
In some ways, it's corroborating your story because it's saying, like, no, he was there.

02:24:12.260 --> 02:24:13.880
He was at S4, he was working on this stuff.

02:24:13.880 --> 02:24:19.760
But we need to get Bob specifically because we know we can have plausible deniability because

02:24:19.760 --> 02:24:22.420
they'll never be able to find his MIT records.

02:24:23.160 --> 02:24:28.400
It turns out that MJ-1, the head of MJ-12, is a guy named Admiral Mike McClellan.

02:24:28.760 --> 02:24:34.960
He wanted to get some of the information out because he didn't want to...

02:24:34.960 --> 02:24:37.940
He thought that some of this information should be out in the public.

02:24:38.300 --> 02:24:40.100
We don't need to keep all this secrecy.

02:24:40.100 --> 02:24:44.020
So he decided, trying to figure out a way to get it to the public.

02:24:44.500 --> 02:24:49.780
So he knew that I was a blabbermouth and I would tell anything I knew.

02:24:51.060 --> 02:24:58.560
They investigated Bob Lazar and they knew that he was a genius, but that he had a background

02:24:58.560 --> 02:25:01.980
such that they could instantly discredit him.

02:25:02.520 --> 02:25:02.940
And then I...

02:25:02.940 --> 02:25:05.380
So I thought about that for a while and I was like, what the...

02:25:05.380 --> 02:25:06.100
What is this?

02:25:06.100 --> 02:25:10.020
And I couldn't even find an Admiral McClellan and then...

02:25:10.020 --> 02:25:12.400
I've heard that name before, but the thing is I...

02:25:12.400 --> 02:25:13.880
That's interesting that you've heard it.

02:25:13.940 --> 02:25:15.800
Yeah, I have definitely heard the name.

02:25:15.880 --> 02:25:19.820
It could have come from John Lear, but I don't know.

02:25:19.940 --> 02:25:25.200
I mean, the thing is, some of the stuff he's saying absolutely can be true or absolutely cannot.

02:25:25.500 --> 02:25:25.780
Totally.

02:25:25.780 --> 02:25:28.940
I don't know, but I mean, you know, I love the guy.

02:25:29.160 --> 02:25:30.740
He was a great friend.

02:25:30.940 --> 02:25:32.160
He just thinks differently.

02:25:33.140 --> 02:25:35.240
And I mean, it's sad he died.

02:25:35.340 --> 02:25:37.180
I wish I had spent more time with him.

02:25:37.380 --> 02:25:37.660
Yeah.

02:25:37.820 --> 02:25:40.520
But after I moved, it was just impractical.

02:25:40.840 --> 02:25:46.640
But yeah, I mean, if you're talking about statements John Lear made, boy, it's tough.

02:25:46.720 --> 02:25:51.760
It's really tough to find out what's accurate and what's not.

02:25:51.760 --> 02:25:54.920
It's decoding the Voynich manuscript or something.

02:25:55.120 --> 02:25:55.360
Yeah, yeah.

02:25:55.440 --> 02:25:58.140
But yeah, no, he's a complicated guy.

02:25:58.440 --> 02:25:59.160
He...

02:25:59.160 --> 02:26:03.300
So I think, and we talked about this a little last night, and maybe this is an interesting

02:26:03.300 --> 02:26:09.660
follow-up for this show, is I think he might have been talking about a guy named Mike McConnell,

02:26:09.820 --> 02:26:11.820
who became NSA director later.

02:26:12.020 --> 02:26:18.780
But he was involved in some S4 Area 51 stuff related to Dan Barish, whose story, I think,

02:26:18.780 --> 02:26:22.420
honestly holds up a lot less than your story.

02:26:23.120 --> 02:26:28.000
But it's, you know, it has to be noted because it's one other guy who's mentioning S4.

02:26:29.560 --> 02:26:33.700
And so Mike McConnell's kind of involved there, and he was a Navy Admiral at the time.

02:26:33.900 --> 02:26:37.960
So I think about that, and I'm like, I wonder if Mike McConnell was somewhat involved.

02:26:38.400 --> 02:26:43.360
When you came out as Dennis, was that a shot across the bow against Dennis Mariani?

02:26:43.580 --> 02:26:44.580
Yeah, sure was.

02:26:44.580 --> 02:26:48.100
So you were trying to kind of get at him a little bit?

02:26:48.200 --> 02:26:48.340
Yeah.

02:26:48.700 --> 02:26:49.100
Yeah.

02:26:49.880 --> 02:26:52.820
What were your feelings towards him kind of personally?

02:26:53.060 --> 02:26:57.980
Were you resentful, or were you, yeah, how'd you feel towards him?

02:27:00.660 --> 02:27:02.460
I guess somewhat resentful.

02:27:05.400 --> 02:27:06.200
I don't know.

02:27:06.440 --> 02:27:09.540
It's hard to tap into how I felt back then.

02:27:09.840 --> 02:27:10.120
Yeah.

02:27:10.120 --> 02:27:15.980
Why do you think, and I know, Luigi, you might have some theories here too, why do you think

02:27:15.980 --> 02:27:21.680
Dennis wanted to meet up with you at the end of this whole saga?

02:27:22.480 --> 02:27:23.020
At the casino.

02:27:23.020 --> 02:27:26.360
And then you meet up with him at the casino, and then you're speaking to him, and Gene Huff

02:27:26.360 --> 02:27:30.160
is looking, and he's just not even, like, looking at you.

02:27:30.200 --> 02:27:31.280
Like, what is that about?

02:27:31.480 --> 02:27:31.920
I don't know.

02:27:31.920 --> 02:27:36.420
I think Dennis really had something to say, and I don't know.

02:27:36.480 --> 02:27:41.100
I don't know if people from S4 got there and changed his mind.

02:27:41.580 --> 02:27:48.900
I don't know if he intentionally wanted me to go out there just to get me away from the

02:27:48.900 --> 02:27:49.240
house.

02:27:49.880 --> 02:27:51.580
I really don't know.

02:27:51.840 --> 02:27:53.780
Because you got back to the house and something had been taken?

