03:02:45.120 --> 03:02:49.020
At those speeds, Einstein's physics takes over from Newton's.

03:02:49.280 --> 03:02:55.380
One consequence is that these screaming, curling outer electrons generate a powerful magnetic

03:02:55.380 --> 03:02:57.660
field just from their own motion.

03:02:57.820 --> 03:03:00.760
And that magnetic field slams into their own spin.

03:03:01.000 --> 03:03:03.760
This is a process called spin-orbit coupling.

03:03:03.760 --> 03:03:06.840
And in bismuth, it's ferociously strong.

03:03:07.140 --> 03:03:12.580
So strong that bismuth's electrons become, in a sense, magnetically self-aware.

03:03:16.580 --> 03:03:21.780
Generating an opposing field in response to anything applied to them from the outside.

03:03:22.080 --> 03:03:25.440
So that's why bismuth has anomalous diamagnetism.

03:03:25.760 --> 03:03:27.480
